      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Michelle Crotty was appointed Deputy Legal Secretary and Head of Operations, Attorney General’s Office in 2015.</p>

<h3 id="education">Education</h3>
<p>Michelle qualified as a solicitor in 1999.</p>

<h3 id="career">Career</h3>
<p>After 8 years in private criminal practice, Michelle joined the Revenue and Customs Prosecution Office and moved to the Crown Prosecution Service when the two offices merged.
In 2010 Michelle joined the Sentencing Council as a legal advisor and in 2011 she was appointed as Head of the Office for the Sentencing Council.
Michelle joined <abbr title="Attorney General's Office">AGO</abbr> in 2014 as the Head of the Criminal Law and Justice Policy Team.</p>

</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_2617">
            <h1 id="deputy-legal-secretary-and-head-of-operations">Deputy Legal Secretary and Head of Operations</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>Deputy Legal Secretary and Head of Operations heads the team that manages the Attorney General’s duties and responsibilities in criminal law, criminal policy development and general casework.  Michelle is also responsible for the business support function. As Deputy Head of the <abbr title="Attorney General's Office">AGO</abbr> she assists the Director General.</p>

</div>
